# <gitmoji> <Imperative summary, ~50 chars> (e.g. "🐛 Fix ghost BLE connections by timing out hung GATT operations")
#
# Why is this change needed, and what would break/be missing without it?
# Wrap body lines around 72 chars. Leave a blank line between summary and body.
#
# - Use the imperative mood ("Fix", "Add", "Modernize"), not past tense.
# - Explain the *why*, not a line-by-line *what* - the diff already shows that.
# - Reference an issue/PR number if one exists (e.g. "Fixes #42").
#
# Gitmoji quick reference (full list: https://gitmoji.dev):
#   ✨ New feature            🐛 Bug fix              🚑 Critical hotfix
#   ♻️ Refactor               ⚡️ Performance          🔒️ Security fix
#   📝 Docs                   ✅ Tests                🎨 Code style/structure
#   🔧 Config                 👷 CI                    ⬆️ Upgrade dependency
#   🔖 Release/version tag    ⏪️ Revert               🔥 Remove code/files
#
# Lines starting with '#' are stripped and won't appear in the commit message.
